LANG FILES

This file controls the name and description displayed in the Field Guide.

Example:

{
"fieldguide.name.fieldguideadditions.rainforest": "Rainforest",
"fieldguide.fieldguideadditions.rainforest.description": "A dense tropical rainforest added by an example datapack."
}

FIELD EXPLANATIONS

Entry Name

Format:

fieldguide.name.fieldguideadditions.<entry_id>

Example:

fieldguide.name.fieldguideadditions.rainforest

This controls the title shown at the top of the Field Guide page.

Entry Description

Format:

fieldguide.fieldguideadditions.<entry_id>.description

Example:

fieldguide.fieldguideadditions.rainforest.description

This controls the text shown beneath the entry image.

IMPORTANT

The <entry_id> must match the ID used in:

examples/example_datapack/data/fieldguideadditions/fieldguide/categories/modded_biomes.json

Example:

{
"type": "virtual_entry",
"id": "fieldguideadditions:rainforest",
"virtual_type": "tutorial",
"icon": "fieldguideadditions:textures/fieldguide/entries/rainforest_page.png"
}

Because the entry ID is:

fieldguideadditions:rainforest

the lang keys must use:

rainforest

Example:

fieldguide.name.fieldguideadditions.rainforest
fieldguide.fieldguideadditions.rainforest.description

If the IDs do not match exactly, the Field Guide will not be able to find the correct name and description.

EXAMPLE

Category Entry ID:
fieldguideadditions:rainforest

Name Key:
fieldguide.name.fieldguideadditions.rainforest

Description Key:
fieldguide.fieldguideadditions.rainforest.description

All three must use the same entry ID ("rainforest").
